Dealing with Finacial Data to the penny

Here is an example where dolars and cents yeild the wrong total
but pennies yeild the correct answer.

Because $0.11 does not have an exact representation in binary we
lose a little each time we use the 0.11 in a calculation.
However since 11 pennies has an exact representation in binary
we lose nothing and we get the sum.

* if we use pennies we need to divide the result 100 or use a format
like I did below;

proc format ;
   picture mkedol (round)
           other  =  '000,000,000' (prefix='.'  mult=0.01)
;run;quit;


data billion;

   retain dollar 0.11 pennies 11;

   * 11 cents;
   * $0.11 dollars;

   do add=1 to 1000000000;
        sum_dollar   +  dollar;
        sum_pennies  + pennies;
   end;

   put sum_dollar  comma18.;
   put sum_pennies mkedol.;

   stop;

run;

109,999,999   We are $1 dollar off
110,000,000   This is the correct answer

